Her first published pictures were by [[Juergen Teller]] for a 1996 issue of ''i-D''.{{Citation needed|date=September 2009}}  She has modelled on the catwalk for [[John Galliano]], [[Christian Dior]], [[Donna Karan]], [[Prada]], [[Gianni Versace S.p.A.|Versace]], [[Miu Miu]], [[Jasper Conran]] <ref>[http://www.jasperconran.com/collections/womenswear/archive/a-w-2007,112,COL.html#nav=path_%252Fcollections%252Fwomenswear%252Farchive%252Fa-w-2007%252C112%252CCOL.html%253Fid%253D35 Jasper Conran Autumn Winter 2007 Collection]</ref>, [[Giorgio Armani]], [[Julien MacDonald]], [[Jean-Paul Gaultier]], [[Badgley Mischka]], and [[Dolce & Gabbana]]. She has worked with many leading fashion photographers including [[Patrick Demarchelier]], [[Steven Meisel]], [[Steven Klein]], [[Nick Knight]], [[Mario Testino]], [[David Sims]], [[Bryan Adams]], and featured in magazines including ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'', ''[[W (magazine)|W]]'', ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]'', ''[[Harper's Bazaar]]'', ''[[Harpers & Queen]]'', ''[[i-D]]'', and ''[[Visionaire]]''.  She was on the January cover of British ''Vogue''.  Since 2005 she has been one of the faces of the British high-street chain [[Marks and Spencer]] and in  2008 she launched the haircare line ''model.me'' for [[Toni & Guy]], alongside [[Jamelia]] and [[Helena Christensen]].{{Citation needed|date=September 2009}}
she is signed to Tess Management in London.

In March 2003, O'Connor was featured in a three-part [[Channel 4]] [[documentary film|documentary]] ''This Model Life''.<ref name="nymag"/>  She writes a column for [[London Fashion Week]] paper ''The Daily Rubbish'', contributes a regular [[blog]] to the British ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' online, has written for ''[[The Sunday Times]]'' and the ''[[Daily Mail]]'', and wrote and presented a [[Radio documentary|documentary]] on fashion, ''Erin's Model World'', for [[BBC Radio 4]].

In 2009{{When|date=September 2009}}, she will appear as a mentor and judge on the Irish [[reality TV]] series ''[[The Model Agent]]'' for [[RTE 2]].

On 20 May 2009, she officially opened the Duncan of Jordanstone College of Art & Design (University of Dundee) VIP degree show preview night, "Designs on the Future", featuring amongst the various disciplines, a fashion show of work from both jewellery and textiles final year students.
O'Connor is the vice chair of the "British Fashion Council" and runs the "Model Sanctuary," an area of relaxation for catwalk models between shows.{{Citation needed|date=September 2009}}

In 2001 she appeared as herself in the "Paris" episode of ''[[Absolutely Fabulous]]''.{{Citation needed|date=September 2009}}


She lives in London.{{Citation needed|date=September 2009}}
